The paper deals with constructing binary embeddings for signals, which is a problem commonly studied in machine learning and signal processing. The use of random projections and order statistics suggests a focus on dimensionality reduction and feature selection, which are key topics in machine learning and information theory (cs.LG and cs.IT). The mention of classification and reduced-dimensionality space further supports this. Additionally, the use of embeddings in computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) is also relevant. Finally, the mention of analytical characterization suggests a potential focus on theoretical computer science (cs.DS).
